DURBAN About 17 children were injured on Monday, when bees attacked them at a school in Umkomaas in Kwazulu-Natal, paramedics said.ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said the swarm of bees attacked the children at a school on Old Main Road.He said paramedics arrived to find several children waiting in a classroom.READ: Schoolchildren stung by bees in Pretoria Paramedics assessed the children and found that 17, aged between 7 and 10, had sustained numerous bee stings, he said in a statement.The children were treated on scene and then taken to various hospitals for further medical care.Meiring said some children had been transported privately, before paramedics arrived.Africa News Agency